The ZIKV vaccines currently under development are mainly based on purified inactivated viruses, plasmid DNA, or mRNA platforms (
 Tebas et al., 2017; 
 Gaudinski et al., 2018; 
 Modjarrad et al., 2018). Importantly, none of these ZIKV vaccine approaches have achieved success in terms of generating highly effective neutralizing antibodies by using prM or E protein alone. Instead, a combination of prM-E structural proteins is required, even if the 
 pr peptide of prM protein might not be present in the final vaccine formulation.
